  "commentary": "With SPX at 7100.86 sitting just below the GEX flip at 7115, dealers are currently in positive gamma territory and likely buying this dip given the PIN regime dynamics. The recent wall break detection suggests we've pushed through a key level, but the strong positive gamma wall at 7100 (+4.3B) should provide immediate support, while the negative gamma zone from 7110-7115 creates a critical inflection point where dealer hedging could amplify moves in either direction. Watch 7115 closely - a break above flips dealers to negative gamma and could trigger accelerated buying toward the major resistance at 7150-7200 where dealers will aggressively sell.\n\nBottom line: expect a bounce from current levels with 7115 as the make-or-break level for further upside.",
